<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06237164 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06237164 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  REAL-ESTATE; QA  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Q I think you goofed recently when you advised that couple not to buy land fortheir retirement home even though they won't retire for about 10 years. Withland costs constantly going up, buying land for a retirement home now makesgood sense, don't you agree?;   A No. At first glance, most people think, asyou do, that buying land for a retirement home now or even buying the hometoday will save money. It will if everything goes exactly according to yourplan. But that rarely happens.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Home  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  ADVICE ON RETIREMENT HOME IS SOUND  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Real Estate; Robert J. Bruss is a Bay Area lawyer and real-estate broker.Write to him in care of the San Jose Mercury News, 750 Ridder Park Drive, SanJose 95190. Sorry, no personal replies.  </MEMO><TEXT>     You should see all the sad letters I receive from widows who own lots theyor their late husbands bought in anticipation of building their retirementhomes. Now the widows can't afford to build or don't want to do so. Variationson this same theme include divorces and illnesses.;   The theory of buying aretirement property now makes sense. But the reality is retirement plans oftenchange and advance purchase of retirement property usually turns out to be aburden instead of a blessing. For this reason, I still advise: Never buy anyproperty you can't use within six months after purchase.; Q I own severalcommercial properties. The woman who usually leases my properties is areal-estate broker. But she is not a Realtor. When I asked her about this, shesaid she sees no advantage to being a Realtor. Do you agree?;   A Areal-estate broker is licensed by the state to sell, lease and manage realestate. He or she can elect, in addition, to become a member of the NationalAssociation of Realtors.;   Realtors have a code of ethics and work to upgradethe real-estate industry.;   Most residential real-estate brokers areRealtors. While there are a few benefits for commercial property specialiststo be Realtors, too, many commercial property brokers find the benefits arenot worth the cost. I agree.; Q Since reading your article a few weeks agoabout the income-tax deduction for depreciation of apartment buildings, Irealized I have not claimed depreciation on my four-unit building. I live inone apartment and rent the other three. How can I claim depreciation on therentals for the last eight years?;   A You can amend your income tax returnsfor the last three years to claim your forgotten depreciation deductions. Thepleasant result should be an income-tax refund. For further details, consultyour tax adviser.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Robert J. Bruss column  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910824  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  5D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  442  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday, August 24, 199100237164,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>